Eno Compton
Developer Advocate, Google
enocom@google.com
@enocom_

* Installation

    $ go get golang.org/x/tools/present

* Getting Started

    $ cat > my-presentations.slide
    Title of document
    Subtitle of document
    15:04 2 Jan 2006
    Tags: foo, bar, baz

    Author Name
    Job title, Company
    joe@example.com
    http://url/
    @twitter_name

    * My first slide
    (CTRL-D to write string to file)

* Start the present tool

    $ present

* Show code!

If we have a file called hello.go in the same directory, then this line in the
slides:

    .code hello.go

* Turns into this:

.code hello.go

* Add other things

Things like:

    .code x.go /^func main/,/^}/
    .play y.go
    .image image.jpg
    .background image.jpg
    .iframe http://foo
    .link http://foo label
    .html file.html
    .caption _Gopher_ by [[https://www.instagram.com/reneefrench/][Ren√©e
    French]]

